               <unclear>case</unclear>
            </del>
            <lb/>
circumstance, when fairly considered<lb/>
there is <hi xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                rend="underline">no principle of general destruction,</hi>
            <lb/>
&amp; there are a number of counterbalancing<lb/>
agencies. - -<lb/>
- - Low islands are forming or are<lb/>
constantly increasing at the mouths<lb/>
of great rivers, from the mixture<lb/>
of the materials of the land, with<lb/>
those of the Sea, &amp; from the opposing<lb/>
agencies of the tide &amp; the Stream. -<lb/>
- Coral rocks are continually forming<lb/>
in the great extent of the ocean,<lb/>
&amp; they are already the bases of<lb/>
many fertile islands in the <rs xmlns:conf="https://www.lancaster.ac.uk/library/ns/digital-library/config/1.0"
                xml:id="ttag1"
